PersonaIntegrationTrigger.description:
A single event trigger declared by an **agent** (`agent.ts`). `on` is a Relayfile-adapter-normalized event name (e.g. `pull_request.opened`, `issue.create`, `message.created`). `match` and `where` are filter sugars the deploy CLI lints against a known registry; unknown values warn but do not fail parse, so the cloud runtime stays the source of truth.

Triggers live on the agent ( {@link  AgentSpec.triggers } ), not the persona — the persona only declares which providers it connects to ( {@link  PersonaIntegrationConfig } ). The deploy CLI joins the two: events from `agent.triggers[provider]`, connection/scope from `persona.integrations[provider]`.

Examples:   { on: "pull_request.opened" }   { on: "pull_request_review_comment.created", match: "@mention" }   { on: "check_run.completed", where: "conclusion=failure" }   { on: "message.created", paths: ["/slack/channels/C_REVIEW/**"] }   { on: "message.created", maxConcurrency: 1 }
